const mergeProfile = (profile, updates) => ({
  ...profile,
  ...updates,
  address: {
    ...profile.address,
    ...updates.address
  }
});


Why this works

...profile → copies all original properties

...updates → overwrites top-level properties (like age)

For nested address, we merge separately:

...profile.address → original nested values

...updates.address → overwrites zipcode + adds country

Example:-
const profile = {
  name: "Charlie",
  age: 29,
  address: { city: "San Francisco", zipcode: "94101" }
};

const updates = {
  age: 30,
  address: { zipcode: "94109", country: "USA" }
};

console.log(mergeProfile(profile, updates));

Output:-{
  name: "Charlie",
  age: 30,
  address: {
    city: "San Francisco",
    zipcode: "94109",
    country: "USA"
  }
}
